AGI&nbsp;- Two hospitals and five territorial districts of Brescia offer work to Ukrainian doctors and health workers who have fled the war. The initiative was taken by Asst Garda who published a call for competition, read by AGI. The document provides for the activation of co-operative enchants > coordinated and continuous with validity until 4 March 2023.
The requirements for access are: Ukrainian citizenship, with residence in Ukraine, before 24 February last; the professional qualification obtained abroad regulated by EU directives; the knowledge of Italian and English; possession of a European passport for refugees. The task is to carry out medical, health and welfare activities: for medical services a fee of 35 euros per hour is expected; while for the health and welfare of 21 euros per hour.&nbsp;
"A concrete sign of closeness to the Ukrainian population - comments the general manager of Asst Garda, Mario Alparone - and at the same time a professional recognition of foreign citizens who through their professionalism can be of help within the territorial health. A way to strengthen organics and ensure all health benefits.”
